getState() - Method in class model.Fleet
Returns a JSONObject instance containing the following values: fleet: a JSONArray with the information returned by the method Ship.getState() of each ship in Fleet.fleet. misses: a JSONArray with the information returned by the method Position.getState() of each position in Fleet.misses. hits: a JSONArray with the information returned by the method Position.getState() of each position in Fleet.hits. occupied: a JSONArray with the information returned by the method Position.getState() of each position in Fleet.occupied.
getState() - Method in class model.FleetDTO
 
getState() - Method in class model.Game
Returns a JSONObject instance containing the following values: level: a String indicating the game's level. players: a JSONArray with the information returned by the method Player.getState() of each player in Game.players. currentPlayer: an int that indicates the index of the Game.currentPlayer in the list of players.
getState() - Method in class model.Player
Returns a JSONObject instance containing the following values: name: a String indicating the player's name. real: a Boolean value that indicates if the player is real. data: the JSONObject returned by Fleet.getState().
getState() - Method in class model.Ship
Returns a JSONObject instance containing the following values: pos: a JSONArray with the information returned by the method Position.getState(). orientation: an int which is either 0 or 1 indicating the ship's orientation. 0 means HORIZONTAL and 1 means VERTICAL. sunk: a Boolean that indicates wether the ship is sunk. placed: a Boolean that indicates wether the ship is placed. length: an int that represents the ship's length. hits: a JSONArray of Boolean values where each value represents a ship's position and takes value 1 if ship was hit there and value 0 otherwise.
